cards.name: Heracross

attacks.name: Single-Horn Throw
attacks.effect: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are heads, this attack does 70 more damage.

cards.description: It loves sweet nectar. To keep all the nectar to itself, it hurls rivals away with its prized horn.

cards.name: Burmy
cards.description:
To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers
itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.

cards.name: Mothim
cards.description: It loves the honey of flowers and steals honey collected by Combee.

cards.name: Combee
cards.description: At night, Combee sleep in a group of about a hundred, packed closely together in a lump.

cards.name: Vespiquen

attacks.name: Reckless Charge
attacks.effect: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

cards.description: It houses its colony in cells in its body and releases various pheromones to make those grubs do its bidding.

cards.name: Cherubi
cards.description: It nimbly dashes about to avoid getting pecked by bird Pokémon that would love to make off with its small, nutrient-rich storage ball.

cards.name: Cherrim

attacks.name: Worry Seed
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

cards.description: As a bud, it barely moves. It sits still, placidly waiting for sunlight to appear.

cards.name: Cherrim

attacks.name: Leech Seed
attacks.effect: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

cards.description: After absorbing plenty of sunlight, Cherrim takes this form. It's full of energy while it's like this, and its liveliness will go on until sundown.

cards.name: Carnivine

abilities.name: Power Link
abilities.effect: If you have Arceus or Arceus ex in play, attacks used by this Pokémon do +30 damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

cards.description: It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.

abilities.name: Forest Breath
abilities.effect: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may take a {G} Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to 1 of your {G} Pokémon.

cards.name: Houndour
cards.description: It is smart enough to hunt in packs. It uses a variety of cries for communicating with others.

cards.name: Houndoom

attacks.name: Corner
attacks.effect: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

cards.description: If you are burned by the flames it shoots from its mouth, the pain will never go away.

cards.name: Heatran

attacks.name: Ragin' Mad Strike
attacks.effect: If this Pokémon has damage on it, this attack does 40 more damage.

abilities.name: Speed Link
abilities.effect: If you have Arceus or Arceus ex in play, this Pokémon has no Retreat Cost.

cards.description: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

cards.name: Marill
cards.description: The fur on its body naturally repels water. It can stay dry even when it plays in the water.

cards.name: Azumarill
cards.description: Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of things in water and tell what they are.

cards.name: Barboach
cards.description: Its two whiskers provide a sensitive radar. Even in muddy waters, it can detect its prey's location.

cards.name: Whiscash

attacks.name: Thrash
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 more damage. If tails, this Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

cards.description: It is extremely protective of its territory. If any foe approaches, it attacks using vicious tremors.

cards.name: Snorunt
cards.description: It is said that several Snorunt gather under giant leaves and live together in harmony.

cards.name: Froslass

attacks.name: Blizzard
attacks.effect: This attack also does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

cards.description: When it finds humans or Pokémon it likes, it freezes them and takes them to its chilly den, where they become decorations.

cards.name: Snover
cards.description: During cold seasons, it migrates to the mountain's lower reaches. It returns to the snow-covered summit in the spring.

cards.name: Abomasnow

abilities.name: Vigor Link
abilities.effect: If you have Arceus or Arceus ex in play, attacks used by this Pokémon cost 1 less {C} Energy.

cards.description: It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.

abilities.name: Snowy Terrain
abilities.effect: During Pokémon Checkup, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, do 10 damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

cards.name: Origin Forme Palkia

attacks.name: Zone Smash
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 more damage.

cards.description: It soars across the sky in a form that greatly resembles the creator of all things. Perhaps this imitation of appearance is Palkia's strategy for gaining Arceus's powers.

cards.name: Phione

attacks.name: Water Pulse
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

cards.description: When the water warms, they inflate the flotation sac on their heads and drift languidly on the sea in packs.

cards.name: Pikachu

attacks.name: Spark
attacks.effect: This attack also does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

cards.description: When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.

cards.name: Raichu

attacks.name: Spark
attacks.effect: This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

abilities.name: Resilience Link
abilities.effect: If you have Arceus or Arceus ex in play, this Pokémon takes −30 damage from attacks.

cards.description: Its tail discharges electricity into the ground, protecting it from getting shocked.

cards.name: Electrike
cards.description: It stores static electricity in its fur for discharging. It gives off sparks if a storm approaches.

cards.name: Manectric

attacks.name: Flash
attacks.effect: During your opponent's next turn, if the Defending Pokémon tries to use an attack, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack doesn't happen.

cards.description: It stimulates its own muscles with electricity, so it can move quickly. It eases its soreness with electricity, too, so it can recover quickly as well.

cards.name: Clefairy
cards.description: It is said that happiness will come to those who see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a full moon.

cards.name: Clefable

attacks.name: Moonblast
attacks.effect: During your opponent's next turn, attacks used by the Defending Pokémon do −30 damage.

cards.description: A timid fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen, it will run and hide the moment it senses people.

cards.name: Gastly

attacks.name: Astonish
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent reveals a random card from their hand and shuffles it into their deck.

cards.description: It wraps its opponent in its gas-like body, slowly weakening its prey by poisoning it through the skin.

cards.name: Haunter
cards.description: It likes to lurk in the dark and tap shoulders with a gaseous hand. Its touch causes endless shuddering.

cards.name: Gengar

attacks.name: Hypnoblast
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

cards.description: To steal the life of its target, it slips into the prey's shadow and silently waits for an opportunity.

cards.name: Unown

abilities.name: CHECK
abilities.effect: Once during your turn, you may choose either player. Look at the top card of that player's deck.

cards.description: Its flat, thin body is always stuck on walls. Its shape appears to have some meaning.

cards.name: Rotom

attacks.name: Dash Attack
attacks.effect: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

abilities.name: Speed Link
abilities.effect: If you have Arceus or Arceus ex in play, this Pokémon has no Retreat Cost.

cards.description: Its electricity-like body can enter some kinds of machines and take control in order to make mischief.

cards.name: Sudowoodo

attacks.name: Fighting Headbutt
attacks.effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon {ex}, this attack does 30 more damage.

cards.description: Although it always pretends to be a tree, its composition appears more similar to rock than to vegetation.

cards.name: Phanpy
cards.description: This Pokémon lives and nests on a riverbank. After playing in the mud, it won't be able to settle down unless it washes its body.

cards.name: Donphan

attacks.name: Rolling Spin
attacks.effect: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Rolling Spin attack does +60 damage.

cards.description: Donphan is covered in tough hide, so even being hit by a car won't faze this Pokémon. However, it is extremely susceptible to rain.

cards.name: Larvitar
cards.description: Born deep underground, this Pokémon becomes a pupa after eating enough dirt to make a mountain.

cards.name: Pupitar
cards.description: Its shell is as hard as bedrock, and it is also very strong. Its thrashing can topple a mountain.

cards.name: Tyranitar

abilities.name: Power Link
abilities.effect: If you have Arceus or Arceus ex in play, attacks used by this Pokémon do +30 damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

cards.description: Extremely strong, it can change the landscape. It is so insolent that it doesn't care about others.

cards.name: Nosepass
cards.description: It moves less than an inch a year, but when it's in a jam, it will spin and drill down into the ground in a split second.

cards.name: Meditite
cards.description: It never skips its daily yoga training. It heightens its inner strength through meditation.

cards.name: Medicham

attacks.name: Kick Shot
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

cards.description: Through yoga training, it gained the psychic power to predict its foe's next move.

cards.name: Gible
cards.description: It skulks in caves, and when prey or an enemy passes by, it leaps out and chomps them. The force of its attack sometimes chips its teeth.

cards.name: Gabite
cards.description: In rare cases, it molts and sheds its scales. Medicine containing its scales as an ingredient will make a weary body feel invigorated.

attacks.name: Linear Attack
attacks.effect: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

cards.name: Zubat
cards.description: It emits ultrasonic waves from its mouth to check its surroundings. Even in tight caves, Zubat flies around with skill.

cards.name: Golbat
cards.description: It loves to drink other creatures' blood. It's said that if it finds others of its kind going hungry, it sometimes shares the blood it's gathered.

cards.name: Crobat

abilities.name: Cunning Link
abilities.effect: Once during your turn, if you have Arceus or Arceus ex in play, you may do 30 damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

cards.description: Both of its legs have turned into wings. Without a sound, Crobat flies swiftly toward its prey and sinks its fangs into the nape of its target's neck.

cards.name: Croagunk
cards.description: Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a poison jab.

cards.name: Toxicroak

attacks.name: Toxic
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned. Do 20 damage to this Pokémon instead of the usual amount for this Special Condition.

cards.description: Swaying and dodging the attacks of its foes, it weaves its flexible body in close, then lunges out with its poisonous claws.

cards.name: Magnemite
cards.description: The electromagnetic waves emitted by the units at the sides of its head expel antigravity, which allows it to float.

cards.name: Magneton
cards.description: Three Magnemite are linked by a strong magnetic force. Earaches will occur if you get too close.

cards.name: Magnezone

abilities.name: Resilience Link
abilities.effect: If you have Arceus or Arceus ex in play, this Pokémon takes −30 damage from attacks.

cards.description: As it zooms through the sky, this Pokémon seems to be receiving signals of unknown origin while transmitting signals of unknown purpose.

cards.name: Mawile

attacks.name: Iron Beam Breaker
attacks.effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a {M} Pokémon, this attack does 30 more damage.

cards.description: It uses its docile-looking face to lull foes into complacency, then bites with its huge, relentless jaws.

attacks.name: Defensive Unit
attacks.effect: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes −20 damage from attacks.

cards.name: Bronzor
cards.description: Ancient people believed that the pattern on Bronzor's back contained a mysterious power.

cards.name: Bronzong

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.effect: This attack does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

cards.description: In ages past, this Pokémon was revered as a bringer of rain. It was found buried in the ground.

cards.name: Origin Forme Dialga

attacks.name: Time Mash
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If tails, during your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

cards.description: Radiant light caused Dialga to take on a form bearing a striking resemblance to the creator Pokémon. Dialga now wields such colossal strength that one must conclude this is its true form.

cards.name: Giratina

attacks.name: Crisis Dive
attacks.effect: Discard 2 random Energy from this Pokémon.

cards.description: This Pokémon is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours, where common knowledge is distorted and strange.

cards.name: Eevee
cards.description: Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

cards.name: Snorlax

attacks.name: Collapse
attacks.effect: This Pokémon is now Asleep.

cards.description: It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.

cards.name: Hoothoot
cards.description: It always stands on one foot. It changes feet so fast, the movement can rarely be seen.

cards.name: Noctowl

attacks.name: Silent Wing
attacks.effect: Your opponent reveals their hand.

cards.description: Its eyes are specially developed to enable it to see clearly even in murky darkness and minimal light.

cards.name: Starly
cards.description: They flock around mountains and fields, chasing after bug Pokémon. Their singing is noisy and annoying.

cards.name: Staravia
cards.description: Recognizing their own weakness, they always live in a group. When alone, a Staravia cries noisily.

cards.name: Staraptor

attacks.name: Brave Bird
attacks.effect: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

cards.description: When Staravia evolve into Staraptor, they leave the flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.

cards.name: Shaymin

abilities.name: Sky Support
abilities.effect: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, your Active Basic Pokémon's Retreat Cost is 1 less.

cards.description: It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.

cards.name: Arceus

attacks.name: Power Blast
attacks.effect: Discard a random Energy from this Pokémon.

cards.description: According to the legends of Sinnoh, this Pokémon emerged from an egg and shaped all there is in this world.

attacks.name: Ultimate Force
attacks.effect: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your Benched Pokémon.

abilities.name: Fabled Luster
abilities.effect: This Pokémon can't be affected by any Special Conditions.

cards.name: Irida
cards.effect: Heal 40 damage from each of your Pokémon that has any {W} Energy attached.

cards.name: Celestic Town Elder
cards.effect: Put 1 random Basic Pokémon from your discard pile into your hand.

cards.name: Barry
cards.effect: During this turn, attacks used by your Snorlax, Heracross, and Staraptor cost 2 less {C} Energy.

cards.name: Adaman
cards.effect: During your opponent's next turn, all of your {M} Pokémon take −20 damage from attacks from your opponent's Pokémon.
